{"image_id": "PMC4839758_7", "image_size": [773, 1000], "ocr": [{"text": "Fine Mapping and Candidate Gene Analysis", "bbox": [534.5, 49.0, 727.3, 60.5]}, {"text": "Table 4. Markers used for genetic mapping of ygl-1.", "bbox": [45.5, 95.4, 286.3, 108.0]}, {"text": "BAC accession number Marker Primer sequence (50-30) Product size (bp)", "bbox": [45.5, 116.1, 727.3, 128.9]}, {"text": "AC194148.5 P1 F:TCTTCATCTCTCTATCAAACTGACA 230", "bbox": [45.5, 135.4, 663.1, 146.9]}, {"text": "R:TGGCACATCCACAAGAACAT", "bbox": [376.5, 151.1, 525.2, 162.7]}, {"text": "AC193998.4 P2 F:GAAGTGGGGAACATGGTTAATGTC 157", "bbox": [45.5, 166.9, 663.1, 178.5]}, {"text": "R:TCACGGTTCAGACAGATACAGCTC", "bbox": [376.5, 182.7, 553.4, 194.3]}, {"text": "AC190890.6 P7* F:TTGTCCCTGCTTGCATGACA 155", "bbox": [45.5, 198.4, 663.1, 210.4]}, {"text": "R:TGGCTCGATCAACTTCCCTG", "bbox": [376.5, 214.3, 524.8, 225.8]}, {"text": "AC193473.4 P8* F:ACGAACAGGAGAACATGCGT 212", "bbox": [45.5, 230.0, 663.1, 242.0]}, {"text": "R:CATGGCAGCCCACATTTGTT", "bbox": [376.5, 245.8, 524.3, 257.4]}, {"text": "AC191330.4 P3 F:CGCCTGTGATTGCACTACAC 161", "bbox": [45.5, 261.6, 663.1, 273.1]}, {"text": "R:CACGCTGTTTCAGACAGGAA", "bbox": [376.5, 277.4, 526.1, 289.0]}, {"text": "AC191330.4 P11* F:CTTCCCAAAAGCCACCCAGA 198", "bbox": [45.5, 293.0, 663.1, 305.0]}, {"text": "R:GTGGATGCTTGCATGACGAC", "bbox": [376.5, 309.0, 527.0, 320.5]}, {"text": "AC201968.5 P12* F:CCTCAACTTCCCCATCTCCG 199", "bbox": [45.5, 324.6, 663.1, 336.6]}, {"text": "R:TGCGCCTAACCTTCGAAGTT", "bbox": [376.5, 340.5, 524.3, 352.1]}, {"text": "AC195193.4 P13* F:CTCATTTTGTTCCAGACCCGC 144", "bbox": [45.5, 356.2, 663.1, 368.2]}, {"text": "R:ACTGGTACCTTTCAGGGCAA", "bbox": [376.5, 372.1, 525.6, 383.7]}, {"text": "AC195193.4 P14* F:GTGCTGTGCATGCGTATCTG 204", "bbox": [45.5, 387.7, 663.1, 399.7]}, {"text": "R:GTACCACCGACCATCCCATC", "bbox": [376.5, 403.7, 526.3, 415.2]}, {"text": "AC195193.4 P9* F:TTTCAGTTCGGCGTCGATCA 227", "bbox": [45.5, 419.3, 663.1, 431.3]}, {"text": "R:GGGCCCGTGTACATGTTACA", "bbox": [376.5, 435.2, 526.5, 446.8]}, {"text": "AC195884.4 P10* F:GAGATCACCAGCCGTTCCTC 191", "bbox": [45.5, 450.9, 663.1, 462.9]}, {"text": "R:GACGATAGGCGGTTCTCGTG", "bbox": [376.5, 466.8, 528.1, 478.4]}, {"text": "AC190859.4 P4 F:TATATTAGAGGCACCTCCCTCCGT 377", "bbox": [45.5, 482.6, 663.1, 494.1]}, {"text": "R:AGCTGCTTCAGCGACTTTGG", "bbox": [376.5, 498.4, 526.0, 509.9]}, {"text": "AC190706.4 P5 F:GTGAGAATCCTTCAGCGGAG 182", "bbox": [45.5, 514.1, 663.1, 525.7]}, {"text": "R:CTGTGGCAGATGTGGTATGG", "bbox": [376.5, 529.9, 527.5, 541.5]}, {"text": "AC205622.1 P6 F:CGTTTGATATGATGTGGAGATTCG 135", "bbox": [45.5, 545.7, 663.1, 557.3]}, {"text": "R:AAGCTTGTGAATGTTCTGGATGTC", "bbox": [376.5, 561.5, 550.9, 573.1]}, {"text": "*, These eight SSR markers came from previous study [39].", "bbox": [45.5, 585.7, 310.5, 597.7]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0153962.t004", "bbox": [45.5, 608.7, 186.2, 620.0]}, {"text": "were used to screen the 34 recombinant individuals detected by markers P2 and P4. A total of", "bbox": [252.5, 638.2, 717.9, 652.1]}, {"text": "12, 7, 5 and 7 plants with crossovers were found with P7, P8, P9 and P10, respectively. Thus,", "bbox": [252.5, 654.6, 711.3, 668.5]}, {"text": "ygl-1 was mapped to an interval of about 0.86 Mb between P8 and P9 (Table 4, Fig 3B).", "bbox": [252.5, 671.0, 685.0, 684.9]}, {"text": "Fine mapping of ygl-1", "bbox": [252.5, 711.6, 395.1, 729.8]}, {"text": "To fine map ygl-1, four new SSR markers polymorphic between the two parents and two DNA", "bbox": [252.5, 736.7, 721.8, 750.6]}, {"text": "pools were identified (Table 4). Meanwhile, 2247 and 2930 plants of F3 and F2 segregating pop-", "bbox": [252.5, 753.1, 726.6, 768.1]}, {"text": "ulations, respectively, were screened to obtain more recombinant individuals. A total of 32", "bbox": [252.5, 769.5, 702.5, 783.5]}, {"text": "plants were confirmed with crossovers by P3 located on the side of P8, including 22 and 10", "bbox": [252.5, 785.9, 704.4, 799.9]}, {"text": "from F3 and F2 populations, respectively. A total of 96 recombinant plants were detected by P9,", "bbox": [252.5, 802.3, 726.1, 817.4]}, {"text": "including 52 and 44 from F3 and F2 populations, respectively. All 133 (32 + 96 + 5) recombi-", "bbox": [252.5, 818.8, 713.0, 833.7]}, {"text": "nant individuals screened by P3 and P9 were genotyped by new polymorphic SSR markers", "bbox": [252.5, 835.2, 702.7, 849.1]}, {"text": "P11, P12, P13 and P14. Finally, only one recombinant was identified both by marker P12 and", "bbox": [252.5, 851.6, 716.8, 865.5]}, {"text": "P13, on the opposite side of ygl-1. Thus, ygl-1 was narrowed down to a genomic region of about", "bbox": [252.5, 868.0, 727.0, 882.0]}, {"text": "48 kb in the B73 genome sequence, flanked by markers P12 and P13 (Fig 3C).", "bbox": [252.5, 884.4, 638.8, 898.4]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0153962 April 21, 2016 8 / 19", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}